Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Agoranax. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 90, 2 or 173, 14. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX CRI 0020.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0709)
